article.headline: UC Irvine 66, Cal Poly 62
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- UC Irvine used a late run in the final two minutes to post a 66-62 victory over Cal Poly on Thursday. Cal Poly led 60-59 with 2:24 to play on a free throw by sophomore guard Trae Clark, but Chuma Awaji's layup with 1:54 to go gave UC Irvine the lead for good at 61-60 and sparked a 7-2 run. Mark Kelley scored 13 points and Darren Fells added 12 to lead the Anteaters (7-8, 1-0 Big West). Cal Poly (6-7, 1-2 Big West) was paced by senior forward Derek Stockalper with 15 points and Tyler McGinn with 12 points. UC Irvine made 45 percent of its shots from the field while holding Cal Poly to just 35 percent. Cal Poly made just eight-of-14 free throws, compared to 18-of-27 for UC Irvine. UC Irvine led by as many as six points and settled for a 26-24 advantage at halftime. The Mustangs led 54-52 with 4:37 to go on a layup by junior forward Matt Hanson and the game was tied at 59-59 with 2:24 to play on Clark's layup. His ensuing free throw for a three-point play gave Cal Poly its last lead at 60-59.
